Product name: VINTAGE large Edward GOREY print / poster 1970s DRACULA and Lucy Vampire Gothic goth Count Dracula gory Moon
Description:
This is a wonderful large-scale print that features the artwork of EDWARD GOREY. The print features an illustration titled DRACULA and LUCY, originally done for the New York Times Book Review. This illustration is much more intricate than Gorey's usual cross-hatch method, and seems to have involved some ink washes as well. The image is striking - Count Dracula in pursuit of a trance-like Lucy, who is emerging from a cave that looks like a creature's jaws! The trees and moon above make it look even more monstrous. 
The print was part of a folio of work published in 1979 - the back bears the number 52 and a smaller illustration from another New York Times illustration.
It measures approx. 15 1/2" x 11" - with the image this large you can really see the intricate line work that Edward Gorey was famous for. It is in overall good condition. There are a few faint "foxing" marks in the white border area (those pale yellow stains common in aging paper).  The print comes well-packed for shipping.
Suitable for framing, this would make a special gift for the Edward Gorey enthusiast, or the perfect addition to your own collection. Just in time for Halloween!
about Edward Gorey: 
A truly prodigious and original artist, Edward St. John Gorey (1925-2000), gave to the world over one hundred works, including The Gashlycrumb Tinies, The Doubtful Guest and The Wuggly Ump; prize-winning set and costume designs for innumerable theater productions from Cape Cod to Broadway; in 1978 he won a Tony Award for Costume design on the Broadway production of "Dracula." A remarkable number of illustrations in publications such as The New Yorker and The New York Times, and in books by a wide array of authors including Samuel Beckett, T.S. Eliot, John Updike, Charles Dickens, Edward Lear, Lewis Carroll, Hilaire Belloc, John Ciardi, Muriel Spark, Edmund Wilson, Peter Neumeyer, Virginia Woolf, H.G. Wells, Florence Parry Heide, Bram Stoker, Raymond Chandler, Gilbert & Sullivan, and many others. His well known animated credits for the PBS "Mystery" series have introduced him to millions of television viewers. Gorey's masterful pen and ink illustrations and his ironic, offbeat humor have brought him critical acclaim and an avid following throughout the world.

Product name: Extremely rare 1940's Hermes belt with shield shaped escutcheon and key details. Amazing!!
Description:
From my personal collection comes this unbelievable original late 1940's Hermes belt. 
As a jewellery collector, I have to say I had a hard time listing this in this "belts" category as it is really a piece of jewellery. The belt is designed to be worn at the natural waist and measures 32" in full length, best suited for a 23-28 inch waist. 
This belt is decorated with 5 shield keyhole escutcheons and finished at the buckle with their signature Hermes key. 
The belt is in amazing condition given the age, but does have some slight oxidation to a couple of the shields. I am happy to provide more photos for interested parties.
This belt would look amazing with high waisted jeans, over a fitted dress, or simply to be enjoyed as a collectors piece. The quality is befitting that of Hermes and it is an amazing treasure.

Product name: Pet loss Necklace, Lock of Hair Necklace, Pet memorial gift, Loss of a Pet, Memorial Jewelry, Glass Floating Locket Fur Ashes Dog Keepsake
Description:
A few tears were shed making this special necklace not long after my beautiful Rocky passed, he was 14 years old and the best thing that ever happened to me ♥ He now has a new home in my heart, and when I wear this necklace, I feel him even closer, like an angel checking up on me from time to time, making sure i'm happy and smiling :)
I would love to spread this gift to others who've also experienced the loss of a pet, a dog or a cat, or maybe a pet snake. If your pet's name is no more than 7 letters in length, I can hand-stamp their name on a beautiful stainless steel heart blank which sits beautifully on top of the fur.
The locket itself is made with a strong magnetic closure so you will be able to open this when you receive the necklace and securely place the fur, hair, ashes or any other tiny ornaments of your beloved that may fit inside. 
The photos above show the front side of the pendant with the hand-stamped heart and the back of the locket which contains a tiny photo that can be placed behind the fur once you've enclosed it inside.
So..... all you need to do is:
1. In the "Note to seller" box at Checkout, include the name of your pet (must be 7 letters or less)
2. Attach the photo you'd like to hold inside your locket via an Etsy Convo to me (or, once you've placed the order at Checkout, use the "Contact seller" link to send me a message with the attached photo).
♥~ ITEM DETAILS ~♥
✤ Glass floating locket is made of stainless steel and measures approx. 1" (30mm) in diameter and 0.2" (5mm) in thickness
✤ Locket frame is complete with a pre-soldered bail used to hang the chain from. 
✤ Necklace features a stunning antique silver angel wing charm measuring approx. 3cm in length. 
✤ Pendant hangs off a dainty stainless steel cable chain, measuring 24" (60cm) in length)
Stainless steel is a great alternative to sterling silver. It is very affordable, hypoallergenic, robust and will not tarnish or change colour over time.

Description:
Are you looking for a special and unique way to celebrate a new baby?  Are you looking for a personal baby shower gift?  Are you looking for a fun way to document your baby's growth? Our monogrammed newborn baby blankets are the prefect way to do just that!  As a photographer, graphic artist and mother for 4, I wanted to create something special and unique for every baby!  I created my first blanket for my own child so that I could lay him on it each month and track his growth each month! :)
Our baby blanket will be custom designed for the baby you are celebrating!  I will work with you to pick out the perfect colors, fonts, words, and design so that together we create something truly one of a kind and personalized to that baby!  Every baby deserves to be celebrated, I would love to help you do that!
Our blankets are printed with archival inks on premium fleece.  The blankets are not only soft and snuggly, but are also durable, standing the test of time. 
RECEIVING BLANKET:  This blanket is a lower pile fleece and has some stretch to it, it is great for swaddling babies up!
HEIRLOOM BLANKET: This blanket is made of superior fleece and is a soft, more fuzzy fleece.  This blanket is an heirloom blanket because it is meant to be snuggled with for years! :)

-----------------------
1 - Upon checkout, please included in the "notes to seller," your baby's First, Middle and Last name.  Also, if you plan to call the baby by something other than the name listed (Ex: "Jackson" but you are going to call him "Jack") or if you are going to call the baby by their middle name.

Product name: 2017 - 2018 Planner
Description:
**PLEASE READ ALL OF THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION BEFORE PLACING YOUR ORDER**
FAQs can be seen on our website at www.plumpaper.com/faq/
__________________________________________________________________
ORDERING PROCESS:
When placing your order, please complete the following steps:
1: Drop Down Menu Selections:
- Weekly Spread Option (Option 1, 2, 3, or 4 - can be seen in 2nd photo of this listing).
- Month you would like your planner to start in.
2. In the "NOTE TO SELLER" box that appears before checkout, please include the following:
- Name for cover 
See "PERSONALIZATION DETAILS” below for specific instructions regarding your name. PLEASE read these details!
__________________________________________________________________
PERSONALIZATION DETAILS:
YOUR NAME:
--- The name will be written in the same style that is on the sample planner of your purchase. If the name is in all lowercase on the sample, we will write your name in all lowercase for your cover.
If you would like the name to be written in a different style than the sample shows, please specify this in the Note to Seller box with a description of what you would like.
NOTES EXAMPLE: "Please write the name in all capital letters: SARAH JEAN" or "Please capitalize only the first letter of each name: Sarah Jean"
IMPORTANT - Your order MUST INCLUDE an explanation if you would like your name written different than the sample shows.
--- If your notes just say "Sarah Jean" without an explanation like the above example, it will be written out just like the sample shows. Therefore, if the sample is in all lowercase, the name on the planner will read "sarah jean". If the sample shows all capital letters, the name on the planner would read "SARAH JEAN”.
--- If you do not want your name on the cover, please specify this in the notes section of your order. (Pattern will continue instead)
YOUR MONOGRAM:
--- Middle letter in a monogram is your last name initial. If your name is "Molly Ann Smith", your monogram should read “MSA".
--- We will write your letters exactly as you write them in your order. If you write "MAS" instead of "MSA", we will put the monogram as "MAS". Please be careful to write your monogram EXACTLY as you want it written.
--- Monogram must be 3 letters.
--- If you do not want a monogram on the cover, please specify this in the notes section of your order. (Pattern will continue instead)
__________________________________________________________________
ADD ONS:
***Please keep our PAGE LIMITS in mind when adding pages and months to your order***
***Ordering more than the maximum page limits can delay the processing of your order.***
Additional Months and Additional Pages are available in our Add Ons section of our shop here:
https://www.etsy.com/shop/PlumPaperDesigns?section_id=12769506&ref=shopsection_leftnav_8
__________________________________________________________________
PRODUCT DETAILS:
4 Weekly Spread Options to choose from.
Option 1: Days broken down by “Morning, Afternoon, and Evening”
Option 2: Days broken down hourly in 30 minute increments
Option 3: Days broken up with just lines in each column
Option 4: Horizontal spread with weekly notes
- This is a 12 MONTH REGULAR PLANNER
- Begins in ANY month you choose
- Planner Size: 7.5" x 9"
- 12 Monthly LAMINATED TABS
- Durable Synthetic Cover (waterproof and tear resistant)
- Personalized Name on Cover
- Week, Month, and Year-at-a-glance pages
- 2 Notes Pages Per Month
- Contacts Page
- Holidays
- 2 Sided Pocket Folder
- The year on the cover will reflect the year/years of the planner ordered.
(example: A planner from August 2014 - July 2015 will have "2014-2015" on the cover)
Changes CANNOT be made to the inside planner page layouts and design.
*Print Color: We do our best to match the colors of the covers shown on the computer screen. Since every monitor is calibrated differently and are vibrant with backlighting, colors may vary in brightness and hue from what is shown.
__________________________________________________________________
CANCELLATION POLICY:
Due to the customization of each planner, we can only cancel orders within 24 hours from when your order is placed.

----------------------------------------------
Answers to Questions You May Have:
----------------------------------------------
When will I receive my order?
I am a made-to-order shop. I create your items after I receive payment. For single items or sets with less than 4 items in them, please allow 1-2 weeks for me to complete your order and prepare it to ship. For larger sets or multiple items (more than 4), I ask that you allow 2-3 weeks for the item to ship. I always ship first class, unless otherwise requested and paid for.
I do my best to complete items in the order that they are received. If you need your item quicker, whether it be for a special event or whatever reason you choose, please let me know! You can choose to pay a rush fee of 10. This is a separate listing that you can request from me. You can just add it to your cart with your order. I will get your order to you by your request date, and will upgrade your shipping to USPS Priority Mail.
While I ask for either 1-2 or 2-3 weeks on items, please know that I always strive to get your items to you as soon as possible. If you have a special event coming, like a birthday or a baby shower, I am super flexible and almost always willing to work with you on your deadline!
Can I change the thread or fabric colors?/Did you design this?
I have no problems changing a color scheme. I can make a blonde a brunette or give someone brown eyes over blue. A red dress can be made purple. Changes like this are no big deal, at all.
BUT
That being said, there is a difference to changing a color compared to changing a design. I am not a digitizer. Sometimes I can do minor design changes. I can leave out a hair bow if it doesn't compromise the hair line, if that makes sense. But beyond minor changes, I am unable to alter designs. I, like you, am a consumer. I buy designs from awesome digitizers to be able to stitch out on finished products. Some digitizers wear a double hat and sell their designs as finished products, so they would be able to change designs. But I only wear one hat!
Will my item look exactly like it does in the listing photo?
Not always, and not necessarily. For bibs, they may differ slightly as the ones shown for appliqué fabric. I use what I have in stock, and try my best to stick with the color schemes presented in the photos. If you have your heart set on a certain fabric, or like the design, but the fabric I happened to use in the example doesn’t work for you, please just say so. I want you to be 100% with your order. For puppets, 99% of the time, they will look exactly as they do in the photo. The only time this changes is for characters like Granny and Red Riding Hood, as their clothing is not made of felt, it is cotton. So the same rule of thumb applies as with the bib applique fabrics. Dress Up Dolls will follow the same rules as Red and Granny.
Do you combine shipping?
Shipping costs will be combined automatically when individual listings are added to your cart and purchased in the same transaction.

Product name: Vintage red phone Iskra ETA 62 - Retro Yugoslavian Rotary Telephone
Description:
Rare Vintage Rotary Telephone - Iskra ETA 62 - Made in Yugoslavia, it was the first completely electro-mechanical telephone in the world (1976.) 
This model here is Iskra ETA 62, today a very rare telephone even in former Yugoslavia.
It is in a fair vintage condition. The red color is just stunning. It has scratches here and there, from everyday use.
Iskra, a company from Kranj in Slovenia (then part of Yugoslavia) was very known by quality of products and their technologically advanced telephones were built with highest quality standards.
A must-have phone for collectors!
 This phone has not been tested, but I suppose it is in working condition, since everything is on its place. However vintage phones worked on a different system (rotary dialing sent the pulses for forming a number) than the modern ones (they use digital signals), so they need to be rewired. 
This can be done by following these instructions:
www.ehow.com/how_7362062_rewire-vintage-telephones-modern-jacks.html
Sold as is!

Olive Wood is deeply contrasted with offset Black Walnut giving this piece a real wow factor. Completed with a polished brass center to really highlight the difference in the two woods.
An enduring symbol of peace, Olive was traditionally worn for weddings and victory celebrations. 
This eye-catching ring measures 5mm wide (approximately the thickness of 3 US Quarters) and has a gently rounded surface. It is 2.5mm thick (about 2 US Dimes). The inside is slightly rounded making this an extremely comfortable wear.
BEAUTIFUL RING - EXCELLENT SERVICE - DELIVERED ON TIME - GUARANTEED
HOW WOOD RINGS ARE MADE
The two sides of the ring are bonded through the brass insert. This locks all the pieces together, and makes a very strong ring.
Each ring is finished with a tough acrylic, and polished to a brilliant shine. This makes the rings waterproof and suitable for daily wear.
CUSTOMIZED WOOD RINGS
If you have a custom request, just send me a message. I'll be glad to work with you.
SIZING YOUR WOOD RING
The wood rings are slightly rounded on the inside for a "comfort fit". They tend to run about a half size larger than standard rings. So if you prefer a nice snug fit, subtract a half size from your normal size.
SHIPPING 
Shipping is free worldwide. When shipping outside the United States, you are responsible for any duties or taxes your country may charge.
WOOD RING WARRANTY
When your wood ring arrives, I hope you love it. And, I hope you're glad you chose my shop. If not, let me know! I'll make you happy. Won't fit; no problem. Clashes with your eye color; no problem. Allergic to wood; no problem. I'll make you happy, or refund your money. Period

Product name: Gold Table Numbers, Wedding Table Numbers, DIY Table Numbers, Wooden Table Numbers,Laser Cut Wedding Decor, Rustic Wedding Table Numbers
Description:
We are in LOVE with these table numbers. Being elevated allows them to be elegantly displayed without taking up much room. They will seamlessly blend in with your centerpiece arrangements. 
These numbers are laser cut from 1/8" recycled fiber board.
Size
They are around 8-9.5" tall (pending on tall letters (see photo with table number four:  f would be a tall letter being 4" tall x 1" wide, and o would be 1" tall x 1" wide) The height depends also on single numbers (ex.1) vs. stacked numbers (ex. 22). The width of these numbers starts at number 1 being 4" wide, to number 17 being 8.5" wide. If we have failed to answer any questions about the size of these numbers please send us a message.
*** Please allow 1-2 weeks lead time. We will do our best to get them to you in a timely matter. We work long hours,  and have many orders to fulfill.
Do they come assembled?
No, if they did... shipping would be a nightmare! We send them out flat. It is easy to assemble. Just slide the number into the base. It's as easy as that!
What colors does it come in?
You can choose the colors from the drop down menu above. We offer gold, gold glitter, silver, silver glitter, rose gold, rose gold glitter, black, and DIY.
What does DIY mean?
DIY means DO IT YOURSELF. This means you will receive the table numbers unpainted. SO, you will be in charge of painting them yourself.
Should I order DIY or painted?
If you are on a budget, or want a color we don't offer... DIY is the best option for you.
***How soon should I order?
We suggest you order 2 weeks prior to your wedding/event. We are quickly approaching wedding season, and will be pressed for time. We work long hours and want to ensure you get your table numbers in plenty of time. If you need a rush order please let us know before purchasing, so we can let you know if it's possible. 
***What information should I give you?
Please leave your wedding date in the "note to seller" section at the time of purchase, as well as a date you'd like to have them by. This will be a great way to keep us on track. Thank you in advance!

{{ Details on Flatware }} 
→ All silverware in the shop is "vintage", meaning it's on its second chance on life. However, please do not expect a brand new & never been used spoon. 
→ I am always willing to send you photos of flatware handle options. Please know that I do my best to be quick but that sometimes my response times can be up to 24-48 hours as I get MANY emails daily. 
→ All product from the shop is FOOD SAFE and approved for use with your everyday flatware. I recommend HAND WASHING, as silver plate can tarnish faster over time if put in the dishwasher frequently. These are made with care, so please wash with care. 
{{ Details on Production and Shipping Times }}
→ Production times vary and I always have them updated in my POLICIES TAB. Around holidays, the shop does get busy and production can take up to 14 days. Production is normally anywhere from 7 to 14 days. I offer Rush production for a 10 fee if you need something out immediately - please contact me for a custom listing.
→ Shipping is set to first class on default. If you would like to upgrade you can do so at checkout, but PLEASE be aware that the shipping speed DOES NOT change the production time. Contact me if you need a faster production time. 
→ For US orders, First Class normally takes around 3 to 7 days and Priority is around 2 to 3 days. For International orders First Class normally takes anywhere from 7 to 21 days depending on your location and customs. Please also be aware you may be responsible for customs fees and duties depending on your country. 
→ Tracking is included with EVERY order. Please check your online receipt to see where your package is during its transit to you. Most countries also update tracking, but once it leaves the US there will be no updates until it reaches your country.

Description:

If you want to start the adventure with arm knitting, look no more - you found the right place:)
Did you ever wonder why arm knitting is so great? It's very simple. The best thing about it, is that all you really need to make beautiful blankets or scarves is a big chunky yarn and your own two hands. 
The merino wool that you can buy in our store is very soft, warm and cozy. It has 23 microns. The yarn is very thick and always looks great. It's silky and not itchy at all so you can be sure that it won't irritate your skin. Our wool is hypoallergenic and antibacterial.

1 stitch is around 3 inches.

Description:
Ringo is a first of its kind ring sizer. Its design makes Ringo virtually invisible, and the memory material Ringo is comprised of makes it vastly more comfortable than metal or hard plastic alternatives. It will perfectly fit to your finger the first time you put it on, and it will continue shaping itself to you as your finger changes size with the seasons. 
Don't spend hundreds of dollars getting your precious ring resized only to have it not fit again in a few months time! Ringo is the easy fix to make any ring fit perfectly, and do so completely unnoticed. Other ring sizers are obviously seen and take away some of the natural beauty of your ring. Don't let this happen to you! Use Ringo to make sure your jewelry doesn't lose any of its luster, no matter the size. 
Ringo is also easy to clean; just wipe it off with a dry cloth to remove any excess oil or dirt. Its slim and simple design does not allow for dirt to collect in any crevices that tarnish your rings. Other ring sizers also need to be applied before you put your ring on, making it a difficult application process. Ringo will easily slide right under your ring after you put it over your knuckle, making it a quick and painless process. 
Each Ringo pack comes with six ring sizers, two small, medium, and large - now any sized ring will fit perfectly (for thicker and thinner rings). Add Ringo to your cart today and start wearing your oversized rings with the confidence and comfort you deserve!

What is Argentium silver?
Argentium silver is 100% recycled and purer, brighter and whiter than platinum, white gold or traditional sterling. It's hypo-allergenic, antibacterial and the perfect choice for those who are sensitive to metals and traditional sterling or white gold. Argentium silver is highly tarnish resistant, low maintenance, easy to care for and simple to keep clean.

MATERIALS
GOLD-FILLED JEWELRY:
- Under normal wearing conditions and with proper care, your gold filled jewelry should last at least 10 years.
- 14kt Gold-Filled jewelry is made by bonding a solid layer of 14kt gold on top of another metal, but this layer is 1000 - 10,000 times thicker than gold plating, resulting in a durable, long-lasting product that looks gorgeous like solid gold.
- Gold-Filled jewelry can also be worn by people with sensitive skin.
STERLING SILVER:
- We use .925 Sterling Silver, which requires polishing from time to time from oxidation. You can easily restore silver back to shine with a polishing cloth or use a polishing lotion for that extra shine.
